Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The elements of the input array `arr` are integers.
- The elements of the input array `arr` are within the range of 0 to 9.

Postconditions:
- Each occurrence of zero in the input array `arr` is duplicated.
- The duplicated zeros are shifted to the right.
- The length of the modified array is the same as the original array.
- Elements beyond the length of the original array are not written.